Package ohos.agp.components.webengine

Provides functions related to the WebView component,

such as WebView.load(java.lang.String). This package also provides callbacks to obtain the web page information and control web page redirects. For details, see WebAgent and BrowserAgent. WebConfig in the package is used to provide web-page-related setting options.

Since:
5
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AsyncCallback<T>
    Returns asynchronous callback data.
    JsCallback
    Provides JavaScript callbacks to be invoked when a WebView callback is executed.
    JsMessageResult
    Responds to the callback on a message pop-up.
    JsTextInputResult
    Responds to the callback on a text input pop-up.
    LocationAccessController.Response
    Responds to the request to access geographical location information.
    Navigator
    Represents the navigator for WebView behavior.
    PickFilesParams
    Describes information about the files to be selected.
    ResourceError
    Describes the web resource loading error.
    ResourceRequest
    Describes the web resource loading request.
    ScaleChangeListener
    Provides a listener that listens for scale changes.
    ScaleController
    Manages and observes scaling of a WebView object.
    WebConfig
    Manages the configuration status of the WebView object.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BrowserAgent
    Assists WebView in processing web content callbacks, for example, processing JavaScript events and website attribute change events.
    CookieStore
    Manages cookies for WebView instances.
    LocationAccessController
    Represents the controller of access to geographical location information.
    ResourceResponse
    Provides a response when the WebView requests a certain resource.
    WebAgent
    Processes the events and notifications of the WebView component.
    WebView
    Represents a component that has the web page access capability.
